1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,410
Years ago I took on a daily writing and broadcasting chore that has totaled, now, more than two thousand scripts.

2
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:12,769
Had I been asked at the time to sign a contract to write two thousand scripts,

3
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:17,570
I would have refused in despair at the enormousness of such an undertaking.

4
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:23,489
But I was only asked to write one, the next one, and that is all I have ever done.

5
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:30,370
The principle of the next mile works for Eric Severide, and it will work for you.

6
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:36,690
The step-by-step method is the only intelligent way to attain any objective.

7
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:43,489
The best formula I have heard for quitting smoking, the one that has worked for more of my friends than any other,

8
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:46,130
I call the hour-by-hour method.

9
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:53,330
Instead of trying to reach the ultimate goal, freedom from the habit, just by resolving never to smoke again,

10
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:56,610
the person resolves not to smoke for another hour.

11
00:00:56,800 --> 00:01:02,930
When the hour is up, the smoker simply renews his resolution not to smoke for another hour.

12
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:09,650
Later, as desire diminishes, the period is extended to two hours, later to a day.

13
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:12,130
Eventually, the goal is won.

14
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:20,050
The person who wants freedom from the habit all at once fails because the psychological pain is more than he can stand.

15
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:21,729
An hour is easy.

16
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,810
Forever is difficult.

17
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:28,449
Winning any objective requires a step-by-step method.

18
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:37,890
To the junior executive, each assignment, however insignificant it may appear, should be viewed as an opportunity to take one step forward.

19
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:43,650
A salesman qualifies for management responsibilities one sale at a time.

20
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:49,489
To the minister, each sermon, to the professor, each lecture, to the scientist,

21
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:58,209
each experiment, to the business executive, each conference, is an opportunity to take one step forward toward the large goal.

22
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:03,489
Sometimes it appears that someone achieves success all at once.

23
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:09,170
But if you check the past histories of people who seemed to arrive at the top suddenly,

24
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:21,890
you'll discover a lot of solid groundwork was previously laid, and those successful people who lose fame as fast as they found it simply were phonies who had not built a solid foundation.

25
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:29,890
Just as a beautiful building is created from pieces of stone, each of which in itself appears insignificant,

26
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:33,729
in like manner the successful life is constructed.

27
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:35,969
Do this.

28
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:41,330
Start marching toward your ultimate goal by making the next task you perform,

29
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:45,969
regardless of how unimportant it may seem, a step in the right direction.

30
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:50,930
Commit this question to memory and use it to evaluate everything you do.
